    <thetext>The first paragraph of &quot;12 Statements&quot; says &quot;A LabelledStatement has no semantic meaning other than the introduction of a label to a label set.&quot;  However, &quot;12.12 Labelled Statements&quot; says that &quot;If the result of evaluating Statement is (break, V, L) where L is equal to Identifier, the production results in (normal, V, empty).&quot;  Therefore, because of the sentence in 12.12, a LabelledStatement has some semantic meaning.</thetext>
